familiar: I would try to think of little rhymes or something personal with the name on the first set of towns I saw to remember them.
memorable: If I had heard of the town in real life or in a book or movie.
unique: If it was something that stood out or if it sounded like a generic town name.
realistic: If it a town name that I had never heard of or definitely knew it was the only town named that.
similar: Most seemed realistic to me since there are so many town names so that one was a little tougher to judge.
comments: It seems like a familiar study but not with town names.
column26: It was interesting and went smoothly.
